text.tspan: Is the probability of a student being a binge drinker the same for males
It is almost certain that male students have a greater probability of
being a binge drinker than female students.
A survey of 17,096 students in US four-year colleges collected information about
drinking behavious and alcohol-related problems. Numbers of male and female
'binge-drinkers' (5+ drinks 3 or more times in the past 2 weeks) are shown below.
